## Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety

CRITICAL: All generated code must guard against null/undefined values before calling array methods.

- Supabase-like data: Always use nullish coalescing:
  - const items = data ?? []
- Array methods: Guard before calling:
  - (items ?? []).map(...)
  - Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
- React useState for arrays/objects: Initialize correctly:
  - const [items, setItems] = useState<Type[]>([])
- API response shapes: Validate:
  - const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Optional chaining: Use for nested objects:
  - obj?.property?.nested
- Destructuring with defaults:
  - const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

