=== TASK ===
# Historical Comparison

## Overview
You are building the Historical Comparison page for Gbox360, a board-facing MVP that enables users to compare Investor Perception Index (IPI) and narrative persistence across historical windows and peers. This page serves as a simple, audit-friendly MVP placeholder for peer benchmarking, wiring together a lightweight set of features that will support future expansion. The page must be robust, guard against null/undefined values, and follow the runtime safety rules described in the project’s mandatory coding standards.

The page should be self-contained for MVP use, with clean interfaces to export artifacts, perform lightweight topic classification, compute a simplified IPI, enforce a canonical NarrativeEvent model, and apply narrative persistence with time-decay. It must be designed with a strong emphasis on auditability, data provenance, and UI clarity to support board-level review.

---

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A Historical Comparison dashboard that presents a side-by-side or tabbed view of IPI and narrative persistence metrics across historical windows and peers. It includes a simple MVP placeholder for peer benchmarking to illustrate relative performance.
  
Goals:
- Allow users to select a target company, historical window(s), and a peer (or none) to compare IPI and narrative persistence.
- Display current IPI, directional movement (up/down/flat), and the top narratives driving the change for each window/peer.
- Provide a mechanism to export audit artifacts (CSV, PDF, JSON) capturing IPI computations, narrative event lists, and references to raw payloads for board review.
- Classify narrative events into topics using rule-based and lightweight embedding approaches (MVP).
- Compute a simplified IPI with transparent provisional weights (Narrative 40%, Credibility 40%, Risk proxy 20%).
- Enforce a canonical NarrativeEvent model to ensure immutability, with fields for source/platform, speaker heuristics, audience class, timestamps, and raw text.
- Compute narrative persistence over time with a configurable decay factor that influences the IPI Narrative component.
- Clearly flag provisional weights in the UI and document them in UI/tooltips.

Connected features and UI guidance:
- Export & Audit Artifacts: Accessible per page and per comparison, exporting artifacts containing IPI computations, narrative event lists, and raw payload references.
- Topic Classification (Lightweight): NarrativeEvents receive a topic tag through rule-based logic plus optional lightweight embeddings for MVP detection.
- Simplified IPI Calculation: Weighted combination as defined; show provisional weight indicators and allow future overrides for demonstration.
- Canonical NarrativeEvent Model: Implement an immutable schema and a function to populate speaker heuristics, audience class, timestamps, and raw text.
- Narrative Persistence & Time-decay: A decay-enabled computation that modulates the Narrative portion of the IPI based on time since each narrative event.

UI elements and how they should look:
- Comparison selector: Dropdowns or segmented controls to pick baseline window vs. comparison window(s) and baseline peer vs. selected peers.
- Side-by-side IPI panels: Each panel shows IPI score, direction arrow, delta, and a small “Why” expansion to reveal top contributing narratives.
- Narrative persistence heatmap or tiles: Visual representation of narrative frequency over time with decay scaling for the IPI Narrative component.
- Top narratives list: Cards showing event details (source, speaker, timestamp, text excerpt, topics).
- Export button: Prominent in the header or within each comparison card to export artifacts.
- Provisional weights indicator: Badge or inline label near the IPI weights with a tooltip describing provisional nature.

Visual guidance:
- Maintain the project’s design language: warm cream/beige background, pastel tile accents, bold typographic hierarchy, and accessible UI contrast.
- Use pastel-tinted tiles to group comparison sections and narrative blocks.
- Emphasize auditability: include “Raw Payload” references as expandable items in the narrative lists and artifacts exports.

---

## Components to Build
- HistoricalComparisonPage
  - Props: companyId, selectedWindows[], selectedPeers[], decayConfig
  - State: selectedWindow, selectedPeer, IPIData[], narratives[], exportStatus
  - Responsibilities: orchestrate data fetch/validation, compute IPI, render UI sections, trigger exports.

- CanonicalNarrativeEventModel
  - Schema (immutable):
    - id: string
    - sourcePlatform: string
    - speaker: { name: string, role?: string }
    - audienceClass: string
    - rawText: string
    - timestamps: { createdAt: string, eventAt?: string }
    - payloadReference: string (raw payload URL or reference)
  - Functions:
    - createEvent(input): NarrativeEvent
    - validateEvent(event): boolean
    - serializeForAudit(event): object

- NarrativeTopicClassifier (Lightweight)
  - Inputs: narrativeEvent (with text)
  - Outputs: topics: string[]
  - Methods:
    - detectTopicsRuleBased(text): string[]
    - applyLightweightEmbeddings(text, indexMap?): string[] // optional
  - Safeguards: guard against null/undefined input; always return [] if no data.

- IPIEngine (Simplified)
  - Inputs: narrativeScore, credibilityScore, riskProxyScore
  - Decay: decayFactor over time applied to Narrative component
  - Outputs: IPIValue: number, components: { narrative, credibility, risk }, provisional: boolean
  - Rules:
    - Narrative component = 0.4 * narrativeScore * decayFactor
    - Credibility component = 0.4 * credibilityScore
    - Risk proxy component = 0.2 * riskProxyScore
    - IPI = Narrative + Credibility + Risk
  - Safeguards: clamp values to plausible ranges [0, 100]; ensure NaN/undefined are treated as 0.

- NarrativePersistenceEngine
  - Inputs: narratives[], decayConfig
  - Outputs: persistenceScore: number, time-decayedCounts: array
  - Behavior: apply exponential decay per narrative event over time; sum contributions to determine Narrative component
  - Safeguards: validate arrays; use Array.isArray checks; guard when missing dates.

- AuditArtifactExporter
  - Functions: exportCSV(data), exportPDF(data), exportJSON(data)
  - Data: IPI components, narratives (with topic tags), raw payload references, window/peer metadata
  - Safeguards: guard null data; produce empty artifacts gracefully.

- DataAdapter (API/DB layer)
  - Data sources: will return data in a mocked or real Supabase-like shape
  - Rules:
    - Always use data ?? [] for list results
    - Validate shapes: Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Endpoints (conceptual):
    - GET /historical-comparison?companyId=&window=&peer=
    - POST /historical-comparison/export
  - Database schema placeholders (see Data Models)

- UI Components
  - ComparisonHeader
  - IPIHeroPanel (per window/peer)
  - NarrativeListCard
  - NarrativeTileGrid (heatmap-like visualization)
  - TopicTag / TopicPill
  - ExportButton
  - ProvisionalWeightBadge
  - EmptyState placeholders with guidance

